  "prompt": "What are the best TED Talks by youth?",
  "response": "TED Talks have featured many inspiring speakers, including youth who have shared powerful and insightful ideas. Here are some of the best TED Talks given by young speakers:\n\n1. **Tavi Gevinson: A teen just trying to figure it out**\n   - **Age at time of talk:** 16\n   - **Summary:** Tavi Gevinson, the founder of the online magazine Rookie, shares her journey of navigating adolescence and the importance of embracing the messiness of growing up.\n   - **Link:** [Tavi Gevinson: A teen just trying to figure it out](https://www.ted.com/talks/tavi_gevinson_a_teen_just_trying_to_figure_it_out)\n\n2. **Zak Ebrahim: I am the son of a terrorist. Here's how I chose peace.**\n   - **Age at time of talk:** 27\n   - **Summary:** Zak Ebrahim, son of a convicted terrorist, discusses his upbringing and the conscious choice he made to pursue a path of peace and non-violence.\n   - **Link:** [Zak Ebrahim: I am the son of a terrorist. Here's how I chose peace.](https://www.ted.com/talks/zak_ebrahim_i_am_the_son_of_a_terrorist_here_s_how_i_chose_peace)\n\n3. **Maya Penn: Meet a young entrepreneur, cartoonist, activist... and more!**\n   - **Age at time of talk:** 13\n   - **Summary:** Maya Penn, a young environmental activist and entrepreneur, showcases her work in sustainable fashion, animation, and activism, inspiring others to make a positive impact.\n   - **Link:** [Maya Penn: Meet a young entrepreneur, cartoonist, activist... and more!](https://www.ted.com/talks/maya_penn_meet_a_young_entrepreneur_cartoonist_activist_and_more)\n\n4. **Malala Yousafzai: What does the future hold for Malala?**\n   - **Age at time of talk:** 16\n   - **Summary:** Malala Yousafzai, the youngest Nobel Prize laureate, discusses her advocacy for girls' education and her vision for the future.\n   - **Link:** [Malala Yousafzai: What does the future hold for Malala?](https://www.ted.com/talks/malala_yousafzai_what_does_the_future_hold_for_malala)\n\n5. **Kennedy LeJeune: 14-year-old prodigy programmer**\n   - **Age at time of talk:** 14\n   - **Summary:** Kennedy LeJeune, a teenage coding prodigy, shares his journey into programming and his goal to inspire other young people to pursue their passions.\n   - **Link:** [Kennedy LeJeune: 14-year-old prodigy programmer](https://www.ted.com/talks/kennedy_lejeune_14_year_old_prodigy_programmer)\n\nThese talks highlight the remarkable insights and aspirations of young individuals who are making a difference in their communities and beyond.",
